In order to work you should also add another "/" which is the end of the namespace prefix. ASBecause this attributes doesn't have anything after the second "/", this namespace prefix is not controlled against the authorized namespaces list. U1&HINTS& ASUse with care or prefer simple attribute names without "/". ASHaving XML node with / (which means end of node) make nugget display difficult in many XML viewer. So no longer use "/".
